column17: The attack occurred at a police station in Khonobod.
column18: 05/26/2009: On Tuesday morning, in Khonobod, Andijon, Uzbekistan, assailants fired rocket-propelled grenades and small arms at a police station, killing one police officer, wounding three others, and causing minor damage to the police station.  Islamic Jihad Union (IJU) claimed responsibility for the attack.
column39: The target of the attack was a police station.
column64: The specific motive for the attack is unknown.
column97: Rocket-propelled grenades and small arms were used in the attack.
column108: The attack caused a minor amount of property damage to the police station.

column135: 05/26/2009: On Tuesday afternoon at about 1400, in Andijon, Andijon, Uzbekistan, a suicide bomber detonated an improvised explosive device on Fitrat Street, killing one police officer and wounding three civilians. Islamic Jihad Union (IJU) claimed responsibility.

column181: The specific motive for the attack is unknown.
